cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DB 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and specifically focuses on synonym discovery from free-text corpus. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also likely as the paper proposes a framework for synonym discovery which is a subtask of information retrieval. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper introduces a novel neural network model for determining synonymity between entities. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also possible as the paper uses a neural network model for synonym discovery. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with structured knowledge discovery which is related to databases.
